  "response_text": "A sunny green park fills the opening view, with bright grass, leafy trees, and a path in the background. From the left, a hand lifts a small red candy cup into the foreground. The cup has a yellow lid and a bold black-and-yellow “Juicy Drop” logo on the front, with the product name “Gummy Dip ’N Stix” and an image of a gummy stick being dipped. The yellow lid flips open, revealing pinkish-red gummy sticks arranged upright around the rim and a round center well filled with red gel. The opened lid stays hinged behind the cup like a little dish-shaped flap, while the hand holds the package steady against the park background.\n\nA second hand reaches in from above and begins using the candy. The visuals repeat the action in three side-by-side panels: a long red gummy stick is held vertically, dipped into the red center gel, lifted out, and dipped again. Each panel shows a slightly different moment of the same dipping motion, emphasizing the gummy stick going down into the sour gel and coming back up.\n\nThe setting changes to an indoor study area. A blue version of the Juicy Drop Gummy Dip ’N Stix cup is held in front of a desk with stacked books, a blue desk lamp, pencils, and a pale wall. Its yellow lid is open, and turquoise-blue gummy sticks circle a matching blue center gel. Again, the action appears in three vertical panels: a hand dips a blue gummy stick into the center well, lifts it, and dips it from different angles. The hand holding the cup remains steady at the bottom while the other hand controls the candy stick.\n\nThe scene then shifts to a skate park. A purple version of the candy cup is held near the edge of a concrete bowl, with a skateboard visible in the background. The yellow lid is open, and red gummy sticks sit around a purple-toned center well. A hand dips a red gummy stick straight down into the gel. A young boy, likely a preteen, appears wearing a black skate helmet with a chin strap and a gray long-sleeve shirt. He brings the red gummy stick to his mouth, eats it, and looks forward with a satisfied, calm expression. Behind him, other kids and bikes are visible around the skate park, with hills and trees in the distance.\n\nThe commercial ends on a bright yellow product display. On the left, large text reads “NEW JUICY DROP GUMMY DIP ’N STIX,” with smaller text underneath: “CHEWY STICKS AND SOUR GEL” and “JUICYDROP.COM.” To the right are several product cups in different colors, including red, purple, blue, and pink, with one red cup open and a red gummy stick standing upright in the center gel. At the top right, a small label reads “New at DOLLAR GENERAL.”",
